article.headline: Marist 82, Siena 75
article.story: POUGHKEEPSIE, N.Y. (AP) -- Jared Jordan had 26 points and 11 assists to help Marist beat Siena 82-75 on Saturday night, the Red Foxes' seventh straight victory. Will Whittington added 20 points for Marist (12-6, 6-4 MAAC). Marist, which has won 10 of its last 12 games, made 15 3-pointers in 33 attempts to tie the school record set this season in an 85-77 victory over Siena at the Pepsi Arena. Whittington was 6-for-14 from 3-point range, and Jordan was 5-for-8. Kenny Hasbrouck and Kojo Mensah each scored 18 points for Siena (9-9, 4-6).
